                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51 Salt Funds/193</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Embassy in Japan</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Japanese Ministry for Foreign Affairs</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Reference is made to the American Embassy’s <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    of March 19, 1938, relating to certain phases of the functioning of the Chinese
                    Salt Administration in the areas occupied by Japanese forces in China, pointing
                    out the substantial American interest in the Chinese Salt Administration and
                    making full reservation in regard to American rights and interests therein.</p>
                <p>In this relation the American Government would welcome assurances from the
                    Japanese Government that it is prepared to accord full respect to American
                    interests in the China salt revenues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-21">June 21,
                            1938</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
